336
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,752
and find out you fired
the cook responsible...

337
00:27:07,835 --> 00:27:11,005
- He's a garbage boy.
- Who made something she liked.

338
00:27:11,089 --> 00:27:13,383
How can we claim to represent
the name of Gusteau

339
00:27:13,466 --> 00:27:15,635
if we don't uphold his
most cherished belief?

340
00:27:15,718 --> 00:27:18,638
And what belief is that,
<i>Mademoiselle</i> Tatou?

341
00:27:18,721 --> 00:27:19,722
Anyone can cook.

342
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:30,316
Perhaps I have been a bit harsh
on our new garbage boy.

343
00:27:30,692 --> 00:27:32,986
He has taken a bold risk

344
00:27:33,069 --> 00:27:37,490
and we should reward that,
as Chef Gusteau would have.

345
00:27:37,824 --> 00:27:40,827
If he wishes to swim
in dangerous waters,

346
00:27:40,910 --> 00:27:42,578
who are we to deny him?

347
00:27:43,663 --> 00:27:45,915
- You were escaping?
- Oh, yeah.

348
00:27:45,999 --> 00:27:50,169
Since you have expressed such
an interest in his cooking career,

349
00:27:50,253 --> 00:27:52,296
