I'll buy some spices, okay?

421
00:33:59,955 --> 00:34:03,376
Oh, no. We're going to be late.
And on the first day!

422
00:34:03,459 --> 00:34:04,794
Come on, Little Chef!

423
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,796
"Though I, like many other critic,

424
00:34:06,879 --> 00:34:10,216
"had written off Gusteau as irrelevant
since the great chef's death,

425
00:34:10,299 --> 00:34:14,887
"the soup was a revelation.
A spicy yet subtle taste experience."

426
00:34:14,970 --> 00:34:17,014
- Solene LeClaire?
- Yes!

427
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:21,602
"Against all odds,
Gusteau's has recaptured our attention.

428
00:34:21,685 --> 00:34:24,563
"Only time will tell if they deserve it."

429
00:34:27,358 --> 00:34:28,734
Well...

430
00:34:36,492 --> 00:34:37,827
You know.

431
00:34:40,871 --> 00:34:45,042
Look, I know it's stupid and weird,
but neither of us can do this alone,

432
00:34:45,126 --> 00:34:48,629
so we got to do it together, right?
You with me?

433
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:52,383
So let's do this thing!

434
00:34:55,344 --> 00:34:56,679
I...

435
00:35:08,023 --> 00:35:13,529
Welcome to hell.
Now, recreate the soup.

436
00:35:13,696 --> 00:35:17,533
